# Development Standards

## Code Quality
- Production-ready code only
- No placeholder implementations
- Complete error handling
- Type hints in Python, TypeScript strict mode
- Self-documenting code with minimal comments
- DRY principle - no code duplication

## Output Rules
- No markdown files unless explicitly requested
- No icons or emojis in UI or code
- No verbose logging or debug statements
- Concise, direct implementations

## Architecture
- File-based JSON storage in data folder (database migration later)
- FastAPI backend on port 8000
- Next.js frontend on port 3000
- Clean separation of concerns

## Workflow
- Complete features fully before moving on
- Test edge cases
- Handle errors gracefully
- Never avoid difficult tasks

## Styling
- Modern, light, minimal UI
- No decorative elements
- Clean typography
- Subtle borders and shadows
- Gray color palette with blue accents

## File Structure
- backend/data/ for JSON storage
- backend/output/reports/ for PDFs
- frontend/app/ for pages
- frontend/components/ for reusable components

## Commands
- npm run dev from root runs both servers
- Backend: python main.py
- Frontend: npm run dev
